{"title":"Intense Sniper goes T-Type, Recluse Comes Back Outta Hiding","link":"https://bikerumor.com/intense-sniper-goes-t-type-recluse-comes-back-outta-hiding/","date":1712792090000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-03-1536x990.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"990\" alt=\"intense sniper t pro and recluse alloy mountain bikes\" /></p>\n<p>While most recent coverage of Intense Cycles has focused on the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/pro-bike-check-aaron-gwins-prototype-intense-downhill-bike-with-i-track-suspension/\">upcoming M1 downhill bike</a> and its 3D-printed alloy subframe, they have two new trail-oriented bikes already out… sorta.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Above, the new Sniper T Pro gets an updated rear triangle for SRAM Transmission compatibility. That means UDH compatibility, too, but that’s not it’s only trick…</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-01.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-01-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"2025 intense sniper t pro with UDH and pressed carbon fiber linkage\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-01-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-01-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-01-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-01-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-01.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The shock linkage is made of pressed carbon fiber, which is made from scrap carbon. That means less waste going to a landfill. The bike has 120mm travel, which is 20mm more than the XC-spec Sniper.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-02.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-02-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"2025 intense sniper t pro with UDH and pressed carbon fiber linkage\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-02-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-02-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-02-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-02-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-sniper-t-pro-02.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Another nice feature comes with spec – it gets size-specific handlebar widths and crank arm lengths. That’s a much-appreciated decision by the product manager that helps the bike fit more riders better. <em>Aaaaaannnnd</em>, every complete bike comes with a full tool kit with everything you need to assemble and adjust the bike, including tire sealant and a shock pump. MSRP on this Pro model is $6,499.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>2025 Intense Recluse trail bike</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-02.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-02-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"2025 intense recluse alloy trail all mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-02-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-02-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-02-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-02-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-02.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Last seen on the market in 2018, the Intense Recluse was a carbon fiber 27.5-wheeled trail bike. Now, for 2025, it appears to be making a comeback with 29er with an alloy frame.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-03.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-03-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"2025 intense recluse alloy trail all mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-03-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-03-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-03-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-03-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-03.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It keeps their JS Tuned dual-linkage suspension design with one-piece rear triangle, which they use on their short- and medium-travel full suss bikes. (The M1 and <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2022-intense-tracer-279-enduro-bike-gets-lower-link-driven-shock/\">latest Tracer enduro bikes</a> have switched to a lower link-driven shock design that brings the center of gravity lower)</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/2025-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-all-mountain-bike-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/2025-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-all-mountain-bike-1-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"2025 intense recluse alloy trail all mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/2025-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-all-mountain-bike-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/2025-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-all-mountain-bike-1-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/2025-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-all-mountain-bike-1-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/2025-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-all-mountain-bike-1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/2025-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-all-mountain-bike-1.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The lower Tange Seiki Technoglide headset bearing cup is external and likely a cost-saving spec decision, but the upper bearing is set into the headtube. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-04.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-04-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"2025 intense recluse alloy trail all mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-04-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-04-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-04-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-04-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-04.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The lower shock mount doubles as the linkage pivot and looks to have a flip chip for adjustable geometry. Rear travel is 140mm, paired with 150mm forks.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-05.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-05-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"2025 intense recluse alloy trail all mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-05-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-05-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-05-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-05-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-2024-intense-recluse-alloy-trail-bike-05.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, when can you get it? More like, <em>where</em> can you get it… the new Recluse is only available in European and Asian markets for now. Check <a href=\"https://global.intensecycles.com/recluse-fs-team/\" target=\"_blank\">their global site</a> for more details and to see all the models.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.intensecycles.com\">IntenseCycles.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/intense-sniper-goes-t-type-recluse-comes-back-outta-hiding/\">Intense Sniper goes T-Type, Recluse Comes Back Outta Hiding</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"7fece3b77238c971c3b9f7138759f9cf3ea4c129a3aecda49f5cab143bf007e2","category":"Cycling"}